                                   CHAPTER 10 : 
                                     Numbers

 A number is an arithmetical value, expressed by a word, symbol, or figure,
 representing a praticular quantity and used in counting and making
 calculations.

 There are many types of numbers broadly categorized as,

  (a) Natural - Numbers starting like 1, 2, 3 and so on.
  (b) Integers - Numbers like -1, -2, 0, 1, 2 and so on.
  (c) Whole - Numbers starting like 0, 1, 2, 3 and so on.
  (d) Rational - Numbers of the form p/q where q!=0.
  (e) Real - A set of all numbers.
  (f) Complex - Number of the form a + b*i.